  "bio_raw": "Susmita Sangeeta Mridha has over three years of teaching experience at the secondary and tertiary levels of education.\nShe had previously served as a Lecturer at the Department of English, Canadian University of Bangladesh from November 2024 – January 2026. She worked as the Co-Advisor of CUB English Language Club and CUB Reading Society and had organized different seminars and cultural programs as a part of her job.\nDuring her studies at BUP, she received two Dean’s Letters of Appreciation for remarkable results in both BA and MA. She obtained her BA (Hons.) in 2019 with CGPA 3.80 and MA in 2020 with CGPA 3.74.\nShe is currently serving as a Lecturer in the Department of English and Humanities (DEH) at the University of Liberals Arts Bangladesh.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Comparative Literature, Psychoanalytic Criticism, Postcolonialism, Gender and Sexuality Studies."
  ],
  "education": [
